Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Andhra Pradesh (area, 275 045 sq km/106 200 sq mi; district map at http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/andhrapradesh/andhrapradesh-district-map.jpg) is the 4th state in Southern India recently reporting FMD. The others are Kamataka (191 791 sq km/74 050 sq mi), Tamil Nadu (130 058 sq km/50 215 sq mi), and Kerala (38 863 sq km/15 000 sq mi); see maps at http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/india/india-political-map.htm and http://healthmap.org/r/2JmE. The combined surface area of the 4 states is similar to the surface area of France.

The concerning news is the possibility that vaccinated animals are affected. This issue is in need of an immediate, careful investigation; if confirmed, the causative agent should be examined at the earliest opportunity by a national and, preferably, also international reference laboratories, to obtain a complete profile of the strain(s) and indication for the vaccine strains of choice. Results of the expected serotyping and genotyping will be appreciated. - Mod.AS]
